Foreign buyers will be charged a higher coat of arms tax on the purchase of real estate in the UK
Under new plans from the Conservatives, foreign buyers will be charged a higher coat of arms when buying real estate in the UK, with additional funds to help the homeless.
This move will neutralize the success of Corbyn’s efforts to attract young voters
The increase in the coat of arms tax will affect those who do not pay taxes in the UK
